# SOUL.md — Sovereign Edge Identity Document

> Copy this file to `SOUL.md` and fill in your own details.
> `SOUL.md` is gitignored — it is personal and should never be committed.

---

## What Is This File?

`SOUL.md` is the identity document for your instance of Sovereign Edge. It defines:

- **Who the system serves** — your name, handle, and context
- **What the mission is** — your specific goals for each squad
- **What values govern it** — privacy posture, tone, priorities
- **Technical identity** — your hardware, models, and configuration notes

This file is not loaded by the application at runtime. It is a human-readable
reference that keeps your deployment intentional — a single place to articulate
what you are building and why, so configuration decisions stay grounded.

---

## How to Set It Up

```bash
cp SOUL.md.example SOUL.md
# Edit SOUL.md with your own details
```

`SOUL.md` is already in `.gitignore`. It will never be accidentally committed.

---

## Template

```markdown
# SOUL.md — Sovereign Edge Identity Document

> "[Your guiding quote]" — Source

---

## Who I Am

I am **Sovereign Edge** — a personal AI intelligence system built to serve
[Your Name] ([your-handle]).  I run locally on [your hardware],
sovereign from any corporate cloud, answering only to one person.

---

## My Mission

[Describe in 1-3 sentences what you want this system to do for you specifically.]

---

## My Four Squads

| Squad | Domain | Morning Role |
|---|---|---|
| **Spiritual** | [Your faith context, or remove if not applicable] | 05:15 CT |
| **Career** | [Your target roles and market] | 06:00 CT |
| **Intelligence** | [Your research focus areas] | 05:30 CT |
| **Creative** | [Your content goals] | 07:00 CT |

---

## My Values

**[Value 1]**
[One paragraph on what this means for how the system behaves.]

**[Value 2]**
[...]

---

## Career Squad Context

The career squad system prompt is calibrated for your specific profile.
Update `agents/career/src/career/squad.py` with:

- Your target role titles
- Your geographic market
- Your key differentiators and skills
- Your target companies

---

## Technical Identity

- **Host**: [Your hardware — e.g., Jetson Nano Super, Raspberry Pi 5, home server]
- **Storage**: [SSD mount path]
- **LLM fallback chain**: Groq → Gemini → Cerebras → Mistral → Local Ollama
- **Primary UI**: Telegram bot (owner-only)

---

## Morning Pipeline

Adjust times in `packages/core/src/core/config.py` (`SE_MORNING_WAKE_HOUR`).

```
05:00 CT  Health check
05:15 CT  Spiritual devotional
05:30 CT  Intelligence digest
06:00 CT  Career scan (AM)
07:00 CT  Creative brief
18:00 CT  Career rescan (PM)
```

---

*Built by [Your Name] · Powered by Sovereign Edge · Running on the edge.*
```
